<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Laurel" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Laurel,</orth> the bay-tree, Laurus nobilis, the emblem of victory and glory: <cit><quote>crowns, sceptres, --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.107" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 107</bibl></cit> (== high distinctions). Adjectively: <cit><quote>l. crown.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.6.34" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 6, 34</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>boughs,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 1.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 74</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>l. victory,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 1.3.100" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 3, 100</bibl></cit> (F<hi rend="sub">2. <bibl n="shak. ant 1.3.100" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 3, 100</bibl> 4</hi> <emph>laurell'd</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>